{
    "id": "1002",
    "product": {
        "product-hier": {
            "product-grp-name": "Mark Mens Printed Regular flit cotton",
            "dept-grp-id": "101"       
        },
        "product-components": {
            "product-details": [
                {
                    "product-id": "10204",
                    "style-id": "101-S",
                    "style-desc": "Small"
                },
                {
                    "product-id": "10205",
                    "style-id": "101-M",
                    "style-desc": "Medium"
                },
                {
                    "product-id": "10206",
                    "style-id": "101-L",
                    "style-desc": "Large"
                }
            ]
        }
    }
}

Details:
id : Product group id set as id so that retreival of product components can be easy. for ex. format shirt may have different sizes, medium, large, small. there is
one product group for specific brand shirt, individual products (Large, medium, small) are bundled under that specific shirt. 
product hierarchy -> gives details around product group name and dept it belongs to. Men shirt can be department
Product components -> will have detaisl around products (SKU) under that product group category
  1. Product id -> Unique SKU number representing item that is sold on store/ecommrece
  2. Style-id -> Merchandise reference hierarchy id -> Here the reference element is through Style attribute
  3. Style-desc -> Decription of that style attribute
  
Sample URL
https://us-central1-gmart-firebase.cloudfunctions.net/app/api/read/1002
